HEADWORD: Nosology
<hw>No*sol"o*gy</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Gr.
<grk>no`sos</grk> disease + <ets>-logy</ets>: cf. F.
<ets>nosologie</ets>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>A systematic arrangement,
or classification, of diseases.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>That branch of medical science which treats of
diseases, or of the classification of diseases.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Nosophen</ent>⟦br⟧
